Question 2: Behavior of Financial Return Data

Part (a)

# set working directory 
path <- "C:/Users/dell/Dropbox"
setwd(path)                                                                 

nasdaqd <- read_csv("nasdaqd.csv")                  # read NASDAQ daily data 
nasdaqd <- select(nasdaqd, Date, `Adj Close`)       # keep only "date" and "adj close" 
nasdaqd <- rename(nasdaqd, Xd = `Adj Close`)        # rename "adj close" -> "Xd"
nasdaqd <- mutate(nasdaqd,
                  l.Xd = lag(Xd, n = 1L),           # lag Xd
                  logRd = log(Xd/l.Xd),             # log return
                  sqrRd = logRd^2,                  # squared (log) return
                  absRd = abs(logRd))               # absolute value of (log) return
nasdaqd <- filter(nasdaqd, is.na(logRd) == 0)       # remove missing value
head(nasdaqd, n = 5L)

nasdaqw <- read_csv("nasdaqw.csv") %>% 
           select(Date, `Adj Close`) %>%
           rename(Xw = `Adj Close`) %>%
           mutate(l.Xw = lag(Xw, n = 1L), 
                  logRw = log(Xw/l.Xw),                     
                  sqrRw = logRw^2, absRw = abs(logRw)) %>%
           filter(is.na(logRw) == 0)

nasdaqm <- read_csv("nasdaqm.csv") %>% 
           select(Date, `Adj Close`) %>%
           rename(Xm = `Adj Close`) %>%
           filter(Date >= as.Date("1995-01-01")) 
nasdaqm <- mutate(nasdaqm, Xm = as.numeric(Xm),     # transfer character to number
                  l.Xm = lag(Xm, n = 1L), 
                  logRm = log(Xm/l.Xm),
                  sqrRm = logRm^2, absRm = abs(logRm)) 
nasdaqm <- filter(nasdaqm, is.na(logRm) == 0)

Question 6: FY 1.10 & 1.11

FY 1.10

S <- 400; TT <- 100
simu.norm <- function(s) {
  
  set.seed(s); r <- rnorm(TT)
  Z <- sqrt(TT)*acf(r, plot = F)[[1]][1]
  Q3 <- Box.test(r, lag = 3, type = "Ljung-Box")$statistic    # Ljung-Box test
  Q3s <- Box.test(r, lag = 3, type = "Box-Pierce")$statistic  # Box-Pierce test
  Q6 <- Box.test(r, lag = 6, type = "Ljung-Box")$statistic
  Q6s <- Box.test(r, lag = 6, type = "Box-Pierce")$statistic
  Q12 <- Box.test(r, lag = 12, type = "Ljung-Box")$statistic
  Q12s <- Box.test(r, lag = 12, type = "Box-Pierce")$statistic
  
  c(Z, Q3, Q3s, Q6, Q6s, Q12, Q12s, use.names = F)
  
}

simu.norm.data <- t(sapply(1:S, simu.norm))    # perform function simu.norm() for S times

hist(simu.norm.data[,1], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rnorm(1e8)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

hist(simu.norm.data[,2], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rchisq(1e8, df = 3)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

hist(simu.norm.data[,3], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rchisq(1e8, df = 3)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

hist(simu.norm.data[,4], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rchisq(1e8, df = 6)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

p <- c(0.01, 0.05, 0.10)

FY 1.11

S <- 400; TT <- 100
simu.t <- function(s) {
  
  set.seed(s); r <- rt(TT, 5)
  Z <- sqrt(TT)*acf(r, plot = F)[[1]][1]
  Q3 <- Box.test(r, lag = 3, type = "Ljung-Box")$statistic     # Ljung-Box test
  Q3s <- Box.test(r, lag = 3, type = "Box-Pierce")$statistic   # Box-Pierce test
  Q6 <- Box.test(r, lag = 6, type = "Ljung-Box")$statistic
  Q6s <- Box.test(r, lag = 6, type = "Box-Pierce")$statistic
  Q12 <- Box.test(r, lag = 12, type = "Ljung-Box")$statistic
  Q12s <- Box.test(r, lag = 12, type = "Box-Pierce")$statistic
  
  c(Z, Q3, Q3s, Q6, Q6s, Q12, Q12s, use.names = F)
  
}

simu.t.data <- t(sapply(1:S, simu.t))

hist(simu.t.data[,1], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rnorm(1e8)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

hist(simu.t.data[,2], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rchisq(1e8, df = 3)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

hist(simu.t.data[,3], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rchisq(1e8, df = 3)), lwd = 2, col = "red")

hist(simu.t.data[,4], breaks = 30, freq = F)
lines(density(rchisq(1e8, df = 6)), lwd = 2, col = "red")
